nodes.bodyText:
When a dependency is specified with @aar, as in:
implementation 'com.amazonaws:aws-android-sdk-mobile-client:2.15.+@aar' 

The value for transitive defaults to false. So, you need to override it, as you are:
implementation ('com.amazonaws:aws-android-sdk-mobile-client:2.15.+@aar') {
    transitive = true;
}

However, if you remove the @aar portion, to become just:
implementation 'com.amazonaws:aws-android-sdk-mobile-client:2.15.+' 

Then transitive is true, by default. And you don't need to specify it yourself.
If there are bugs in picking up transitive dependencies from there, we should fix the pom.xml file in the SDK build, to correctly model the needed dependencies.

