nodes.bodyText:
Ah, gotcha, hm, that makes sense.
To test multiple configs, we'll either have to build some teardown in to the Amplify facade, or not use it, in tests. (This way, we're not "stuck" with whatever the first instance of new PredictionsCategory() happens to have, in that static field inside of Amplify.) We could just rework our tests to go against the Category, directly. This would make our tests much more of real-life "integration" tests.
In other words, like:
PredictionsCategory predictions = new PredictionsCategory();
predictions.addPlugin(new AWSPredictionsPlugin());
CategoryConfiguration predictionsConfiguration =
    AmplifyConfiguration.fromConfigFile(context, Resources.getRawResourceId(".../path/..."))
        .forCategoryType(CategoryType.PREDICTIONS);
predictions.configure(predictionsConfiguration, context);
predictions.initialize(context);

