nodes.bodyText:
Possible, add a LOG.info(...) inside here "using defaults...". User might have accidentally written like interPret or something, and be confused that their badly-spec'd config isn't getting read in.
Also, consider enum-ing all the valid config keys:
enum ConfigKey {
    INTERPRET("interpet"),
    ...
}

etc.
This would allow you to validate that nothing weird snuck in, e.g.
for (jsonKey : jsonKeys) {
    try {
        ConfigKey vaildKey = ConfigKey.lookup(jsonKey);
    } catch (InvalidArgumentException noSuchConfigKey) {
        // Tell user what the valid config keys are ...
        // And kindly ask them to refrain from using other ones ...
    }
}

